      • forEach

        public boolean forEach(Processor<? super Result> consumer)
        Description copied from interface: Query
        Process search results one-by-one. All the results will be subsequently fed to a consumer passed. The consumer might be called on different threads, but by default these calls are mutually exclusive, so no additional synchronization inside consumer is necessary. If you need to process results in parallel, run forEach() on the result of Query.allowParallelProcessing().
        Specified by:
        forEach in interface Query<Result>
        Parameters:
        consumer - - a processor search results should be fed to.
        Returns:
        true if the search was completed normally, false if the occurrence processing was cancelled by the processor.
